    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In domine Dei eterni. Anno ab incarnatione domini nostri Iesu Christi
                        millesimo nonagesimo, quinto idus septembris, inditione tertiadecima. Ego
                            <persName
                            key="#Count #Comitatus #Lombard #marriage #childOf #dominus/seniorOf #Curtes #Hay/fodder #Animals #Forests #Slave_labour #Churches"
                            ref="#people/2181">Ubertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filius</rs> quondam <persName
                            key="#Count #Comitatus #parentOf #Lombard" ref="#people/2149"
                            >Erduini</persName> itemque comitis de <geogName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#estates/161"><rs key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus #Count" ref="#places/53"
                            >Parmense</placeName></geogName> qui professus sum lege vivere <rs
                            key="#Lombard">Langobardorum</rs> presens presentibus dixi: Vita et mors
                        in manu Dei est, melius est enim hominem in metu mortis vivere, quam spe
                        vivendi subitanea morte perveniri. Et ideo decrevimus sponte aliquid agere
                        ut temporali vita deficiente in eterna beatitudine eternaliter gaudeamus.
                        Qua propter placuit michi consilio <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelium</rs> meorum
                        pro anima mea et <rs key="#marriage">coniugis</rs> mee <persName
                            key="#marriage"><name ref="Imilda">Imilde</name></persName> quasi
                        proprie iure concedere et potestatem dare <rs key="#Abbots">abbati</rs> et
                            <rs key="#Monks">monachis</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Abbots #Monks #Curtes #Hay/fodder #Animals #Forests #Slave_labour #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti Benedicti</orgName> Deo in <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2004">Sancti
                            Iusti</orgName> et in ecclesia <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2066">Sancti Viti</orgName> et suis omnibus <rs
                            key="#Slave_labour">servientibus</rs>, in <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Hay/fodder #Animals #Forests #Slave_labour #Churches"
                            ref="#estates/2077"><rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> nostra de <placeName
                                ref="#places/2475">Medula</placeName></geogName>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder #Animals">pascuis</rs> et <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silvis</rs> ad sufficientiam utendi; insuper de hominibus illorum terra
                        commorantibus, ne gratia hospitandi supradictis hominis suos gravaremus
                        potestatem hospitandi et per vim ad ullum placitum compellendi omni modo
                        refutamus. Si quis hanc nostram constitutionem confringere temptaverit <rs
                            key="#Penalty">centum librarum argenti pena</rs> nostra institutione
                        dannabiliter mulctetur. Et si contingerit quod predicta curte nostra ab
                        aliis extraneis hominibus per qualicumque modo evenerit et suprascriptam
                        observantiam confringere termptaverit, iam nominata pena mulctetur et omne
                        ius proprietate de eadem curte amittat; et insuper habeat maledictionem Dei
                        atque omnium sanctorum et paciat pena sicut Iuda et Dathan et Abiron. Si ex
                        supradicto reatu ad satisfactionem non venerit, perpetualiter condempnetur
                        quia sic est nostra bona voluntas. Hanc enim <rs key="#Ordinatio">cartulam
                            ordinationis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Notary #Writer #Ordinatio"><name ref="Albertus/notarius"
                                >Albertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> domini regis tradidit et scribere rogavit in
                        qua subter confirmans <rs key="#Witness ">testibus</rs>que obtulit
                        roborandum. Actum in loco <placeName ref="#places/2944">Manerva</placeName>
                        feliciter. Ego Ubertus comes. <persName key="#Witness #Ordinatio #childOf"
                                ><name ref="Albertus">Albertus</name></persName> filius <persName
                            key="#parentOf"><name ref="Wibertus">Wiberti</name></persName> et
                            <persName key="#Witness #Ordinatio"><name ref="Gherardus/de Regio"
                                >Girardus</name></persName> de <placeName ref="#places/191"
                            >Regio</placeName>, <persName><name ref="Rainerius/de Insula"
                                >Raginerus</name></persName> de <placeName>Insula</placeName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Ordinatio"><name ref="Paganus/de Medula"
                                >Paganus</name></persName> de Medula et <persName
                            key="#Judge #Witness #Ordinatio"><name ref="Deusdedit/iudex"
                                >Deodatus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs> ad istam subscriptionem fuerunt. Signum manibus
                            <persName key="#Witness #Ordinatio #Lombard"><name ref="Bernardus"
                                >Bernardi</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Ordinatio #Lombard"><name ref="Marchesus"
                            >Marchesi</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Ordinatio #Lombard"><name ref="Bonus"
                            >Bononis</name></persName> rogati testes lege Langobardorum viventes.
                        (S.) Ego qui supra Albertus notarius domini regis rogatus <rs key="#Writer"
                            >scripsi</rs> post tradita complevi et dedi. </ab>
